  <main class="shell">
    <section class="hero">
      <div>
        <div class="code"><strong>429</strong><span id="status-category">Rate limiting</span></div>
        <h1 class="title" id="status-main-title">Too Many Requests</h1>
        <p class="subtitle" id="status-summary">The WAF is online and intentionally slowed this client because the request volume crossed the configured threshold.</p>
        <div class="meta">
          <div class="meta-item"><span id="meta-request-label">Request ID</span><strong id="req-id">n/a</strong></div>
          <div class="meta-item"><span id="meta-client-label">Client IP</span><strong id="client-ip">n/a</strong></div>
          <div class="meta-item"><span id="meta-time-label">Timestamp</span><strong id="req-time">n/a</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="body">
      <article class="card accent">
        <h2 id="what-happened-title">What happened</h2>
        <div class="state-grid">
          <div class="state"><div><strong id="client-title">Client request</strong><span id="client-text">The current request rate is higher than the allowed burst or sustained quota.</span></div><span class="pill bad" id="client-label">Rate limited</span></div>
          <div class="state"><div><strong id="waf-title">WAF layer</strong><span id="waf-text">The WAF is active and defending the upstream from overload or abuse.</span></div><span class="pill ok" id="waf-label">Protecting</span></div>
          <div class="state"><div><strong id="upstream-title">Upstream service</strong><span id="upstream-text">The upstream remains available behind the rate limit shield.</span></div><span class="pill ok" id="upstream-label">Protected</span></div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2 id="what-next-title">What to do next</h2>
        <ol class="list" id="suggestions-list">
          <li>Wait briefly before retrying.</li>
          <li>Reduce polling, retries, or bursty client behavior.</li>
          <li>Tune per-site rate limits if this traffic is legitimate.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="footer" id="status-footer">TARINIO handled this response with an internal fallback page so the failure mode stays readable.</div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  <div class="powered"><a href="https://github.com/BerkutSolutions/tarinio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Secured by Tarinio</a></div>
